# Installation Guide

**Complete setup instructions for gb-leakage-cmb: from zero to running MCMC chains.**

This guide covers environment setup, dependencies, cosmological codes (CAMB/CLASS), likelihood data, and sampler configuration.

---

## 🚀 Quick Start (TL;DR)

```bash
# Clone repository
git clone https://github.com/GeometricCosmo/gb-leakage-cmb.git
cd gb-leakage-cmb

# Create environment
python -m venv venv
source venv/bin/activate  # On Windows: venv\Scripts\activate

# Install dependencies
pip install --upgrade pip
pip install -r requirements.txt

# Download likelihood data
# (See data/README.md for detailed instructions)
mkdir -p data/{planck,act_dr6,spt3g}
# Download Planck/ACT/SPT files into respective directories

# Verify installation
python tests/test_pipeline.py

# Run a test MCMC chain
python -m analysis.mcmc_driver --config examples/test_planck_only.ini --n_steps 100
```

**Estimated time:** 1–2 hours (mostly waiting for likelihood downloads)

