## 📋 Prerequisites

### **System Requirements**

| Component | Requirement | Purpose |
|-----------|-------------|---------|
| **OS** | Linux (recommended) or macOS | Scientific toolchain compatibility |
| **Python** | ≥ 3.9 (3.11 recommended) | Core language |
| **Compiler** | gfortran + gcc | Building CAMB, scipy |
| **MPI** | Optional (OpenMPI or MPICH) | Parallel MCMC |
| **Disk space** | ≥ 5 GB | Likelihoods + chains |
| **RAM** | ≥ 8 GB | MCMC, N-body analysis |

### **OS-Specific Setup**

#### **Linux (Ubuntu/Debian)**

```bash
# Update package manager
sudo apt update && sudo apt upgrade -y

# Install compiler toolchain
sudo apt install -y \
    build-essential \
    gfortran \
    git \
    wget \
    python3-dev \
    python3-venv

# Optional: MPI support
sudo apt install -y libopenmpi-dev openmpi-bin

# Optional: HDF5 support (for large datasets)
sudo apt install -y libhdf5-dev
```

**Verify installation:**
```bash
gfortran --version
gcc --version
python3 --version
mpirun --version  # If MPI installed
```

#### **macOS**

```bash
# Install Homebrew (if not already installed)
/bin/bash -c "$(curl -fsSL https://raw.githubusercontent.com/Homebrew/install/HEAD/install.sh)"

# Install compiler toolchain
brew install gcc gfortran openmpi open-mpi

# Install HDF5 (optional)
brew install hdf5
```

**Verify installation:**
```bash
gfortran --version
gcc --version
python3 --version
```

#### **Windows (WSL2 Recommended)**

Windows users should use WSL2 (Windows Subsystem for Linux 2):

```bash
# In WSL2 terminal, follow Linux (Ubuntu) setup above
# Then create venv and proceed
```

**Alternative:** Use Docker (see section below).

