## 🔧 Step 7: Install MontePython (Optional)

MontePython is a sampler for MCMC analysis. Only needed if you plan to run MCMC fits.

```bash
# Clone MontePython
git clone https://github.com/brinckmann/montepython_public.git montepython
cd montepython

# Install Python dependencies
pip install -r requirements.txt

# Configure for your system
# (MontePython uses manual configuration in 'montepython/default.conf')

cd ..
```

**Configuration:**
```bash
# Edit montepython/default.conf
# Set paths to CAMB, likelihoods, etc.
# Example:
# path['camb']     = '/path/to/CAMB'
# path['root']     = '/path/to/gb-leakage-cmb'
# path['data']     = '/path/to/gb-leakage-cmb/data'
```

